@node GADG "Gadgets on the main screen."

The biggest part of the main screen is used for the dateview. It shows you
what appointments you have planned and whats on your todo list. All this info
is sorted by date.


You can use a doubleclick to view/edit appointments and todo items or change
the reference date. If you have set the view to period a change of the
reference date becomes imediatly visible in the dateview.


Assistant offers you 4 different dateviews:

day		The dateview shows only the reference date.

week		The dateview shows the week in which the reference is located.
		A week always starts at Monday and ends at Sunday.
		
period		The dateview shows a period around the reference date. This
		period can be controlled from @{"Preferences" link RSET}. You
		have control over the number of days before and after the
		reference date.
		
month.		The dateview shows the month in which the reference date is
		located. A month dateview always starts at the first of the
		month.
		

You can change the reference date by clicking on a calender at the bottom of
the screen. To change the month and year the calender displays you can use
the <, >, << and >> gadgets. To set the reference date to today hit the today
gadget. The goto gadget is used to move you to any date quickly.

@endnode


@node MENU "Menus on the main screen."

Assistant uses the following menu:


Project

     Prefs	Bring up the @{"preferences" link RSET} panel.
     Print	Print the currently selected overview.
     Hide	Hide the screen. It can be reopened by hitting the hotkey.
     About	Shows the programs @{"Copyrights" link COPR}.
     Quit	Quit the program.


Add

     Todo	Bring up the @{"Todo" link RTOE} editor.
     Address	Bring up the @{"Address" link RADE} editor.
     Appoint	Bring up the @{"Appointment" link RAPE} editor.


List

     Todo	Bring up the @{"Todo" link RTOL} list.
     Address	Bring up the @{"Address" link RADL} list.
     Appoint	Bring up the @{"Appointment" link RAPL} list.


Special

     Units	Bring up the @{"Unit conversion" link RCON} utility.

@endnode


@node PANE "The controle panels."

To get input from you Assistant uses the following controle panels:

  @{"Preferences         " link RSET}

  @{"About Assistant     " link RABO}

  @{"Date Calculator     " link RTIC}

  @{"Unit Converter      " link RCON}

  @{"Todo Editor         " link RTOE}

  @{"Address Editor      " link RADE}

  @{"Appointment Editor  " link RAPE}

  @{"Todo List           " link RTOL}

  @{"Address List        " link RADL}

  @{"Appointment List    " link RAPL}

  @{"Address Selection   " link RADP}

  @{"General requester   " link RDEF}

@endnode


@node HIST "A look at the past."

A history overview:

v 0.90 First beta release.


v 0.95 Second beta release.

  * Added keyboard support to the addresslist. If you hit a character or
    digit the list is now moved to the first item starting with that
    character or digit.
  * No need to have a progdir tooltype in the as-start icon.
  * Added keyboard shortcuts for add/list todo/address/appointment.
  * Escape key in main window now does a hide.
  * Fixed bug in time editor. It was possible to type 24:xx hours!
  * The settings menu item is now called prefs.
  * Fixed bug in address list. If you selected edit and then ok the program
    was in an endless loop.
  * The helpkey now also works when you are in a string gadget.
  * If you hit enter/return in a stringgadget the next one is activated. This
    feature was already available with the TAB key but most of you hit return
    a lot easier.
  * The unit conversion now sets its output to 'not set' if a conversion can
    not be made.
  * Dumped my default requester. The current one has the same look as the rest
    of the program. It also understands escape and return/enter keys.
  * Added 'Add Todo' and 'Add Appoint' gadgets for those who can't find the
    menu or the hotkeys :-)


v 1.00 First public release.

  * Resolved conflict with CycleToMenu. There was a deadlock when Assistant
    refreshed its screen titlebar. The screentitlebar is now covered with a
    borderless window with a screendrag gadget in it. It makes date refreshes
    faster to.
  * If a requester has to be put on the public screen to tell the user about
    some problems its now centered to the current viewing area. Thanx Jean-Michel.
  * All menus and gadgets that cause a window to be opened now end with '...'.
  * Corrected names of months.
  * Corrected a bad helpfile reference.
  * Corrected the version string. The date was not layouted properly.
  * Removed a couple of memory leaks.

@endnode


@node FUTU "A look at the future."

Assistants future will depend mostly on opinions and suggestions of its
users. If nobody thinks it is a usefull program not many features will be
added. If a lot of people like the program however new releases will be made.
The best way to make sure that assistant gets the features YOU need is by
sending a list of suggestions to the @{"author" link COPR}.


The following things are already planned for the next release:

* Diary.
* Menuhelp.
* Locale support.
* Check for overlapping appointments.
* Automatic reminder. Reminds you about appointments and todo items upfront.
* Unlimited length comment fields for appointments and todo items.
* More time periods, time references and conversions.
* User can add time periods, time references and conversions


Other features under concideration are:

* Biorithm display.
* Birthday calender.
* Gadgethelp on KS 3.0+
* City distance calculator.
* Enhanced addressbook with user defined fields and changeable layout.

@endnode


@node RSET "Preferences."

The Preferences panel is used to set your preferences. Currently you have the
following options:


Period -	Sets the number of days before the reference date that the
		calender display shows when you have selected period overview.

Period +	Sets the number of days after the reference date that the
		calender display shows when you have selected period overview.

Sceenmode	Shows the currently selected screenmode that Assistant
		should use.

Select		Bring up the Amiga screenmode requester to change the selected
		screenmode. This requires WB 2.1 or up.
	
@endnode


@node RABO "About Assistant."

The about panel shows you info on Assistants @{"copyrights" link COPR}.


@endnode


@node RTIC "Date Calculator."

The date calculator can help you to go from one date to another. You can set a
specific time from the references and add or subtract periods. This way it is
easy to change a date from today to the same day next week.


References	Select one of these to set the current date to a reference date.
	
Periods		Select one of these. Then use the + and - gadgets to add or
		subtract this period from the current date.

Date		The current date. Edit it by hand or use References, periods,
		+ and - to change it.
	
+		Add the selected period to the current date.
	
-		Subtract the selected period from the current date.

@endnode


@node RCON "Unit converter."

The unit converter allows you to convert between different measurement units.
It allows you to transform Fahrenheit to Centigrade or from Gallons to Litre.


Unit system	Use this to select a system of related units.
	
Source unit	Set this to your source unit.
	
Dest unit	Set this to the unit you want your value converted to.
	
Source value	Type the value for your source unit here.
	

If you have selected everything correct the program will calculate the
number of dest units that correspond to your selected number of source units.

@endnode


@node RTOE "Todo Editor."

The todo editor is used to add or change todo items.


Subject		What is this todo item about. This text is also presented
		in the dateview.

Date		At what date has this todo item to be done.

Time		At what time has this todo item to be done.

Calc		Brings up the @{"Date calculator" link RTIC} to make certain date
		changes easier.
		
Repeat		What kind of @{"repeattype" link RETY} do you want to use for this
		todoitem.

Times		How many times do you want the item repeated.

@endnode


@node RADE "Address Editor."

The address editor is used to add or change addresses.


Name		Who is this.

Address		Where does he or she live.

Zip		Whats his/hers zipcode

City		What city?

phone		And last but not least whats the phone number?

@endnode


@node RAPE "Appointment Editor."

The appointment editor is used to add or change appointments.


Subject		What is this appointment about. This text is also presented
		in the dateview.
		
With		A list of people that you have the appointment with.

Add name	Add someone to the with-list.

Del name	Remove the selected person from the with-list.

Date		When do you have the appointment.

Time		At what time does the appointment start.

Until		At what time does it end.

Calc		Brings up the @{"Date calculator" link RTIC} to make certain date
		changes easier.
		
Repeat		What kind of @{"repeattype" link RETY} do you want to use for this
		appointment.

Times		How many times do you want the appointment repeated.

@endnode


@node RTOL "Todo List."

The todo list panel lists all current todo items. This makes selecting a
todo item that is not in the calender listview easier.


add	Add a new todo item to the list.

Del	Remove a todo item from the list.

Edit	Edit an existing todo item.

@endnode


@node RADL "Address List."

The addresslist shows you a list of all addresses.


add	Add a new address to the list.

Del	Remove an address from the list.

Edit	Edit an existing address.

@endnode


@node RAPL "Appointment List."

The appointment list panel lists all current appointments. This makes
selecting an appointment that is not in the calender listview easier.


add	Add a new appointment to the list.

Del	Remove an appointment from the list.

Edit	Edit an existing appointment.

@endnode


@node RADP "Address Selection."

The address selection panel is used to select addresses or names. It is
currently only used to add people to the withlist of an appointment.

You can select an address by clicking it in the listview. Cancel the requester
with cancel or add a new address with new.

@endnode


@node RDEF "General purpose requester."

The general requester has two forms:


Program message		Tells you about something and waits for you to confirm
			that have read it.
	
Information request	Asks you for an Ok/Cancel reply to a question.
	

Confirmation		The request can be confirmed with the enter/return key
			or by hitting 'ok' with the mouse.

Cancelling		The request can be cancelled with the escape key,
                        closing window with the closewindow gadget or by
                        hitting 'Cancel' with the mouse.

@endnode


@node RETY "Repeat types."

Assistant has the following repeat types:


No repeat	Do not use any repeat.

Daily		Repeat the event the next day for a selected number of days.

Weekly		Repeat the event on the same day next week for a selected
		number of weeks.

Bi-weekly	Repeat the event every two weeks for a certain number of
		times.
		
Monthly		Repeat the event on the same day of the month for a selected
		number of months. If the date is not available for certain
		months those months will be skipped.
		
Yearly		Repeat the event on the same date for a selected number of
		years. If the date is not available for certain years those
		years will be skipped. (feb-29)
		
Day/Week	Repeat the event on the same day and week of a month for a
		selected number of months. If this combination is not
		available for certain months those months will be skipped.
		This is used for example to repeat something every 2nd
		wednesday of the month.

@endnode
